issue.summary: User information about extended chr20 region that might help to draw contigs together
issue.status_text: Will attempt to use the information provided to improve the tpf in the region
issue.description: We are currently mapping a zebrafish mutant on chromosome 20. Our region of interest is spanned by Zv9_scaffold2826 through Zv9_scaffold2844 and we would appreciate any extra information you have on this region. Specifically, we know that scaffolds 2826,2827&2828 form a contig; 2830 doesn't link to anything; 2829links to 2831, 2832& 2833. 2834, 2835 & 2836 don't link to anything, and neither does 2842. 2840& 2841 form a contig, and 2843&2844 form a contig. Any information linking these contigs or providing an orientation for these contigs, or any additional markers other than z5335_1, z15841 & z46574 in this region would be most useful. We are also aware that there are several zebrafish mutations published in this region, however none correspond to our mutant.
issue.resolution_text: na
